From: AliceVision-for-Mac port <alex@bsa.ai>
Subject: [PATCH] start.sh: portable realpath (drop GNU `readlink -f`)

macOS ships BSD readlink, which does not accept `-f`. The original line:

    export MESHROOM_ROOT="$(dirname "$(readlink -f "${BASH_SOURCE[0]}" )" )"

errors out on Darwin with "readlink: illegal option -- f".

Use a Python one-liner via `os.path.realpath` for portability. python3
is a hard prerequisite of Meshroom (the very next non-comment line
invokes `python3 "$MESHROOM_ROOT/meshroom/ui"`), so this adds no new
dependency. The Python invocation correctly resolves symlinks in every
path component, matching `readlink -f` semantics on GNU coreutils.

--- a/start.sh
+++ b/start.sh
@@ -1,5 +1,8 @@
 #!/bin/bash
-export MESHROOM_ROOT="$(dirname "$(readlink -f "${BASH_SOURCE[0]}" )" )"
+# Portable realpath: macOS BSD readlink lacks -f. python3 is required
+# by the next line anyway, so we reuse it here. Matches `readlink -f`
+# semantics on Linux (resolves symlinks in every path component).
+export MESHROOM_ROOT="$(dirname "$(python3 -c 'import os, sys; print(os.path.realpath(sys.argv[1]))' "${BASH_SOURCE[0]}")")"
 export PYTHONPATH=$MESHROOM_ROOT:$PYTHONPATH
 
 # using existing alicevision release
